{
  "stem": "12494.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIDE CONVERSATION]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were-- there were many things that were going on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sort of hard to believe, maybe, for you, and sometimes even for me, that the period of three months of March 19 through June 30, 1944 was probably more heavily loaded with events and impact on-- on my life than any other-- not three months, but any other three year period.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- there were many things that were going on and in which I was involved.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One was rescue activities.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Deportations in the Hungarian countryside started, I believe, on May 10.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe the 9th or 11th, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's when the deportations started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What does that mean?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What that meant was that as Hungary was occupied on March 19, and some parts of Hungary weren't occupied until March 20 and 21, very soon thereafter came not only the decree about the Jewish star, but also the ghettoization decrees throughout the country, except Budapest.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Budapest was not ghettoized, except as I mentioned before, in June.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so-- and very soon, on-- as I say, around May 10, the deportations started.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course we have numerous refugees coming from the countryside, those who were not caught, who came to Budapest and had to be looked after.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There had to be people helped to come from the countryside to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was an intense trade in false papers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All of us who, you know, had-- had the ability to get them had false papers, so that we could appear as Jews on the one hand or as-- as non-Jews on the other hand.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had two sets of papers with me all the time, a Jewish set of paper here, and the-- and the non-Jewish set of papers here.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
